dct_title_s: Noua orbis terrarum delineatio singulari ratione accommodata meridiano tabb. Rudolphi astronomicarum
dct_description_sm: From: Tabulae Rudolphinae ... / Ioannes Keplerus. [Ulmae? : s.n., 1659?]. In Latin. In lower right corner: Sumptus faciente Jo: Kepplero. Sculpsit Norimbergæ J.P. Walch A⁰. 1630. World map on central hemisphere and two adjoining half spheres embraced by a double-headed eagle. Shows the Dutch discoveries on the west coast of Australia of Hartog and Houtman. Relief shown pictorially.
